&lt;h2 id="part-1">Part 1&lt;/h2>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Solve the &lt;a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/knapsack%20problem">knapsack problem&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;hellip;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&amp;hellip;&lt;/p>
&lt;p>But really, you are given a set of tiles (which all happen to be some subset of a 3x3) and a set of constraints&amp;ndash;a MxN grid and how many of each tile to place. Count how many constraints are possible.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Tiles may be rotated and/or flipped.&lt;/p>&lt;/blockquote></description></item></channel></rss>